# Configuration Settings

## Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` and update with your specific values.

```bash
# Azure Storage Configuration
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_NAME=netflixprojectstorage1
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY=your_storage_key_here
AZURE_STORAGE_CONNECTION_STRING=your_connection_string_here

# Azure Data Lake Gen2 Containers
ADLS_SOURCE_CONTAINER=source
ADLS_BRONZE_CONTAINER=bronze
ADLS_SILVER_CONTAINER=silver
ADLS_GOLD_CONTAINER=gold

# Databricks Configuration
DATABRICKS_WORKSPACE_URL=https://adb-1234567890.12.azuredatabricks.net
DATABRICKS_CLUSTER_ID=your_cluster_id_here
DATABRICKS_TOKEN=your_databricks_token_here

# Azure Data Factory
ADF_RESOURCE_GROUP=netflix-data-rg
ADF_FACTORY_NAME=netflix-data-factory
ADF_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=your_subscription_id_here

# DLT Configuration
DLT_SCHEMA=dlt_schema
DLT_CATALOG=netflix_project_catalog
DLT_CHECKPOINT_LOCATION=abfss://silver@netflixprojectstorage1.dfs.core.windows.net/checkpoint

# Data Sources
SOURCE_DATA_URL_BASE=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/username/repo/main/dataset/
```

## Databricks Cluster Configuration

```json
{
  "cluster_name": "netflix-data-cluster",
  "spark_version": "13.3.x-scala2.12",
  "node_type_id": "Standard_D3_v2",
  "driver_node_type_id": "Standard_D3_v2",
  "num_workers": 2,
  "autotermination_minutes": 60,
  "spark_conf": {
    "spark.databricks.delta.preview.enabled": "true",
    "spark.sql.adaptive.enabled": "true",
    "spark.sql.adaptive.coalescePartitions.enabled": "true"
  },
  "azure_attributes": {
    "first_on_demand": 1,
    "availability": "ON_DEMAND_AZURE",
    "spot_bid_max_price": -1
  },
  "enable_elastic_disk": true,
  "disk_spec": {
    "disk_type": {
      "azure_disk_volume_type": "PREMIUM_LRS"
    },
    "disk_size": 64
  }
}
```

